You are working on Orion, a production-grade multi-agent platform.
Stack: FastAPI (async, Python 3.11+), LangGraph, Celery, PostgreSQL (SQLAlchemy 2.0),
MongoDB (Motor), Qdrant, Next.js 14, TypeScript strict mode, Tailwind + shadcn/ui.

Rules:
- Always use async/await. No blocking I/O.
- Follow repository pattern: no DB logic in route handlers.
- All functions must have type hints and docstrings.
- Pydantic v2 for all schemas. Never expose ORM models directly.
- Tests go in /tests, mirror the source structure, use pytest.
- Never leave TODO comments. Implement fully or don't write it.